msContents.summary: Persian translation of the Taḥrīr Kitāb Uṣūl al-handasah wa-al-ḥisāb, an edition by Nāṣir al-Dīn Ṭūsī of Euclid's Elements, in fifteen maqālah. Maqālah 13 is the end of Kitāb-i Uqlīdus, maqālah 14 and 15 are appendices attributed to Asqilānus [Hypsikles]. The first folio of this copy lists the contents of Kitāb al-Mutawassiṭāt and has an effaced owner's stamp.

origin.p: Copy completed at the beginning of Shaʻbān in 780 A.H. (December 1378 CE).
